The White House hosted a forum called "Generation Next" to give millennials a platform to voice their opinions and concerns. Around 200 young men and women attended the event, which included discussions with senior administration officials and an interview with President Donald Trump. Topics covered included taxes, trade policy, free speech on college campuses, jobs, tax cuts, workforce development, opioid addiction, and immigration. The President emphasized the need for opportunities for all types of workers, including a push for vocational schools. The event aimed to support the next generation of American entrepreneurs and policy advocates.